From 93ce9016e963227c9d37abf4ca03d6ff04b9ce80 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 14:38:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C (rebuild): native Comments API for the PR diff
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wires the diff sub-mode's Monaco editors into the workbench's stock
`ICommentService`. End state: existing GitHub review comments render
as native CommentThread widgets in the diff, the native `+` glyph
appears on every line, and clicking it opens the standard input that
posts via `IPullRequestProvider.postReviewComment`.

Components:

- `KrtPrCommentThread` (new): minimal `CommentThread<IRange>` impl.
  Mirrors `MainThreadCommentThread` without the extension-host RPC
  surface — KRT's data is shell-out, not extension RPC. Phase 9.5
  had to translate model lines via a `realLines` map; Phase 10's
  URI strategy makes model line == real file line on both sides
  (file:// for modified, krt-git:// for original — both full
  content), so that map is gone.
- `KrtPrCommentController` (new, replaces the Phase 9.5 attempt):
  implements both `ICommentController` (so `ICommentService`
  delegates to it) and a small KRT-side facet
  (`IKrtPrCommentController`). Maintains:
    metadataByUri  (URI → { prUrl, side, path, headSha })
    commentsByPr   (PR → KRT-side comment list)
    threadsByUri   (URI → owned thread instances)
  `KrtPrMultiDiff.setPullRequest` registers per-side URIs on mount;
  the editor pane calls `setCommentsForPr` after each
  `loadReviewComments` resolve and `clearCommentsForPr` on PR
  switch. The controller computes thread sets per URI, reusing
  thread instances by `threadId` so the native widget keeps its
  expanded/collapsed state across re-renders. Snapshots fan out via
  both `updateComments` (inline widgets) and `setWorkspaceComments`
  (the bottom Comments panel) — the granular `updateComments` path
  alone leaves the panel empty on first attach.
- Submit `Action2`: registered against `MenuId.CommentThreadActions`
  with `commentController == 'krt-pr'` so it only shows on KRT
  threads. The thread widget invokes the action with
  `{ thread, text, $mid: CommentThreadReply }` — pull `thread` +
  `text` and route to `controller.submitNewComment`, which posts via
  `IPullRequestProvider.postReviewComment`, appends to
  `commentsByPr`, then re-renders the URI's threads (drops the
  template, adds the realised one).
- Singleton registration is `Eager` so the controller is attached to
  `ICommentService` before any KRT pane sets input.

URI metadata:
- LEFT side anchors at `file.previousPath` (matters on rename).
- RIGHT side anchors at `file.path`.
- GitHub returns review-comment locations with the same convention
  (`c.location.side` + `c.location.path`), so matching is direct.

Stubs (Phase E will fill in):
- `updateCommentThreadTemplate` (drag to extend a template's range)
- `deleteCommentThreadMain` (delete a thread)
- `toggleReaction` (emoji reactions)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
